<html>

<head>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type"
content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1">
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 2.0">
<title>Press Release - Garden Encyclopedia</title>
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 2.0">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<div align="center"><center>

<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="600">
    <tr>
        <td><b>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</b><p><font size="2"><strong>Contact:</strong><br>
        Brian Cronkhite<br>
        Public Relations Coordinator<br>
        Books That Work<br>
        (415) 843-4402<br>
        Internet: </font><a href="mailto:bcronkhite@btw.com"><font
        size="2">bcronkhite@btw.com</font></a></p>
        <h3 align="center">Books That Work Expands Outdoor
        Product Line<br>
        With The Release of <i>Garden Encyclopedia</i></h3>
        <h4 align="center"><i>New Multimedia Guide Provides
        Powerful<br>
        Search Capabilities to Select the Perfect Plants for Your
        Garden</i></h4>
        <p align="left">PALO ALTO, Calif., May 1, 1995 -- Books
        That Work, a leading multimedia software publisher of
        home and garden titles, announced today the release of
        Garden Encyclopedia. Garden Encyclopedia features a
        highly intuitive interface and powerful search
        capabilities that make it easy for anyone to select the
        right plants for their garden. Garden Encyclopedia
        contains more than 1000 annuals, perennials, bulbs,
        vegetables, shrubs, and groundcovers. Color photographs
        and important attributes such as growing zone, bloom
        season, and sun requirements make Garden Encyclopedia a
        virtual at-home nursery. Garden Encyclopedia is available
        on CD-ROM for WindowsTM at retail computer software
        stores nationwide for around $30.00. This is the
        fifteenth release in Books That Works' library of home
        and garden titles. </p>
        <p>Garden Encyclopedia's interface provides a logical
        method for browsing plants or rapidly executing searches
        based on flower color, bloom season and sun requirements.
        Because the common names for plants can refer to multiple
        plants, the program contains audio clips of the correct
        pronunciation of botanical plant names. This allows you
        to select the right plant when visiting the nursery. The
        program also lets you to create, save, and print
        customized plant lists. Pest and disease control
        information is included to help maximize growing success.
        </p>
        <p>Garden Encyclopedia also offers instruction on care,
        planting and propagation techniques using how-to video
        segments complete with narration. In addition to the
        video clips and text, there are more than two dozen lists
        of plants that share an interesting characteristic such
        as &quot;plants that attract hummingbirds&quot; or
        &quot;plants that thrive in heat&quot;. </p>
        <p>Garden Encyclopedia is a fast, practical reference
        tool that saves you time and money by providing expert
        information and tools to select plants that will thrive
        in your garden. </p>
        <p><b>System Requirements</b></p>
        <p>Garden Encyclopedia requires a CD-ROM drive, a 386 IBM
        PC or 100% compatible, 4MB RAM minimum; VGA monitor with
        256 colors, and Windows 3.1. </p>
        <p>Books That Work, Inc., based in Palo Alto, CA, is an
        award-winning developer and publisher of interactive
        software for home consumers. The titles focus on projects
        and activities such as gardening, home improvement and
        other home productivity activities. To order products or
        for more information, contact Books That Work, 2300 Geng
        Road, Bldg. 3, Suite 100, Palo Alto, CA 94303. Phone:
        (800) 242-4546 or visit the Books That Work World Wide
        Web site at <a href="http://www.btw.com/">http://www.btw.com/</a></p>
        <div align="center"><center><pre>#	#	#</pre>
