<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<div align="center"><center>

<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="600">
    <tr>
        <td><b>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</b><p><font size="2"><strong>Contact:</strong><br>
        Brian Cronkhite<br>
        Public Relations Coordinator<br>
        Books That Work<br>
        (415) 843-4402<br>
        Internet: </font><a href="mailto:bcronkhite@btw.com"><font
        size="2">bcronkhite@btw.com</font></a></p>
        <h3 align="center">Books That Work Releases Version 2.0
        of the Award-Winning<br>
        <i>Home Repair Encyclopedia</i></h3>
        <h4 align="center"><i>CD-ROM for Windows Software Takes
        the Guesswork <br>
        Out of Home Repairs and Common Home Maintenance</i></h4>
        <p align="left">PALO ALTO, Calif., March 27, 1995 --
        Books That Work, a leading multimedia software publisher
        for home and yard, announced today the release of an
        upgraded version of <i>Home Repair Encyclopedia</i>. This
        enhanced 2.0 version is a comprehensive reference tool
        providing step-by-step instructions for over 100 home
        projects. These topics cover home maintenance, repair,
        and safety to help users trouble-shoot the most common
        household problems and keep their homes running
        economically and efficiently. <i>Home Repair Encyclopedia
        2.0</i> is based on the award-winning previous version
        which is currently the country's No. 1 best-selling home
        improvement title, and a recent finalist for the 1995 <i>Multimedia
        World's</i> Readers' Choice Award. <i>Home Repair
        Encyclopedia 2.0</i> is available on CD-ROM for Windows
        at retail computer and software stores nationwide for
        around $30.00. Registered users of the original version
        can upgrade to 2.0 for $14.95.</p>
        <p>Significant enhancements for version 2.0<i> </i>include:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Expanded Coverage of Key Subjects - In-depth
                information on plumbing and electrical repairs
                based on customers requests and market research. </li>
            <li>New Topics - More than double the content of the
                original version with additions such as deck
                building, and spring and fall projects.</li>
            <li>Full-motion Video - Detailed how-to instructions
                with professionalvoice-overs and printable text
                scripts are supplemented by more than 90
                illustrative animations.</li>
            <li>Material Estimators - 8 new estimators for
                calculating everything from energy and lumber
                cost, to estimating the materials needed for your
                wallpaper, drywall or tiling project, to
                determining the correct wire gauge and the size
                of your wiring box.</li>
            <li>Enhanced Search Options - Powerful keyword and
                topic search capabilities for finding <i>Money
                Saving Tips</i>, <i>Tips About Old House Repairs</i>,
                videos and animations.</li>
        </ul>
        <p><i>Home Repair Encyclopedia 2.0. </i>is a fast,
        practical reference tool that saves homeowners time and
        money by providing users with information to get the job
        done right the first time.</p>
        <p><b>System Requirements</b></p>
        <p><i>Home Repair Encyclopedia 2.0 </i>requires a CD-ROM
        drive, an IBM PC or 100% compatible, 386 or higher, 2MB
        RAM minimum; VGA or Super VGA monitor, and Windows 3.1. </p>
        <p>Books That Work, Inc., based in Palo Alto, CA, is an
        award-winning developer and publisher of interactive
        software for home consumers. The titles focus on projects
        and activities such as gardening, home improvement and
        other home productivity activities.</p>
