<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<div align="center"><center>

<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="600">
    <tr>
        <td><b>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</b><p><font size="2">Contact:<br>
        Brian Cronkhite<br>
        Public Relations Coordinator<br>
        Books That Work<br>
        (415) 843-4402<br>
        Internet: </font><a href="mailto:bcronkhite@btw.com"><font
        size="2">bcronkhite@btw.com</font></a></p>
        <blockquote>
            <p align="center"><font size="4"><b>Books That Work
            Expands Product Line</b></font><br>
            <b>With the Release of Country Living Gardener:<br>
            Great Home Gardens and Country Living Style</b> </p>
            <p><b>PALO ALTO, Calif., November 11, 1996</b> Books
            That Work, the leader in home and garden consumer
            software, today released two new CD-ROM titles,
            Country Living Style and Country Living Gardener:
            Great Home Gardens. Country Living Style offers the
            essence of country inns, gardens, antique stores and
            a museum together in an easy to navigate format for
            inspiring new decorating ideas. Country Living
            Gardener: Great Home Gardens provides stunning
            photographic tours of lush and vibrant gardens,
            complete helpful hints from the country's most
            illustrious home garden designers. Both titles are
            published and distributed by Books That Work in
            connection with Country Living magazine a leading
            lifestyle publication. </p>
            <p><b>Country Living Style</b><br>
            Country Living Style includes photographs, video
            demonstrations, detailed instructions, and diagrams
            illustrating the beauty of the country living
            lifestyle. Commentary from interior decorators,
            architects, homeowners, and Country Living magazine
            editors make this a great resource for decorating,
            cooking and crafts projects. </p>
            <p>Country Living Style, awarded the Editor's Choice
            for Top 100 software products by HomePC magazine,
            also offers more lifestyle information with a direct
            connection to the Internet and the HomeArts web site.
            </p>
            <p><b>Country Living Gardener: Great Home Gardens</b><br>
            With Country Living Gardener: Great Home Gardens you
            can meet the nationally renowned gardeners of ten
            stunning gardens. This CD-ROM features an
            encyclopedia with nearly 500 plants and resources
            listing sources and societies, by plant. An easy to
            use main menu lets you create a personalized scrap
            book, explore gardens, browse featured plants and
            learn new tips and techniques. Garden tours are
            presented with maps, photographs, narration,
            interviews and text. This title also provides
            Internet capabilities to link to the HomeArts web
            site for more creative home resources on World Wide
            Web. </p>
            <p>Previously available direct from Hearst New Media,
            Country Living Style and Country Living Gardener:
            Great Home Gardens are now available on CD-ROM for
            Windows at retail computer software stores nationwide
            for around $30.00. The two products can also be found
            sold as a bundle for around $50.00. </p>
            <p><b>Country Living Magazine</b><br>
            Country Living Magazine is a lifestyle publication
            devoted to the traditional style of the American home
            and family life. It focuses on American country
            decorating and includes editorial on furnishings,
            cooking, antiques, home building, real estate, and
            travel. </p>
            <p align="center"># # # </p>
