<title>Sash Repair Terms</title>
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 2.0">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<div align="center"><center>

<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="600">
    <tr>
        <td><h2 align="center"><img
        src="../../../headgifs/headbar.gif" alt="Books That Work"
        width="545" height="24"></h2>
        <h2 align="center"><font face="Arial">Sash Repair Terms</font></h2>
        <dl>
            <dt><a name="double"><font face="Arial"><b>Double-Hung
                Windows </b></font></a></dt>
            <dd><a name="double"><font face="Arial">Windows with
                tow operable sashes that slide in vertical
                channels.</font></a><font face="Arial"> </font></dd>
            <dd><font face="Arial"></font>&nbsp;</dd>
            <dt><a name="sash"><font face="Arial"><b>Sash </b></font></a></dt>
            <dd><a name="sash"><font face="Arial">On a window,
                the frame that holds the glass.</font></a></dd>
            <dd><font face="Arial"></font>&nbsp;</dd>
            <dt><a name="strip"><font face="Arial"><b>Parting
                Strip </b></font></a></dt>
            <dd><a name="strip"><font face="Arial">On a
                double-hung window, the wooden strip that
                separates the two sashes. Also called the parting
                bead.</font></a></dd>
            <dd><font face="Arial"></font>&nbsp;</dd>
            <dt><a name="weight"><font face="Arial"><b>Sash
                Weight </b></font></a></dt>
            <dd><a name="weight"><font face="Arial">Iron
                counterweight that balances a double hung sash.
                The weights hang on a cord that goes over a
                pulley in the window frame and ties to the sash.
                Newer double hungs use several different
                spring-loaded sash balance systems.</font></a><font
                face="Arial"> </font></dd>
        </dl>
        <h3 align="center"><font face="Arial">Return to </font><a
        href="window.htm"><font face="Arial">Repairing Broken
        Sash Cords</font></a></h3>
