<title>Press Release - 3D Landscape 2.0</title>
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 2.0">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<div align="center"><center>

<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="600">
    <tr>
        <td><b>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</b><p><font size="2"><strong>Contact:</strong><br>
        Brian Cronkhite<br>
        Public Relations Coordinator<br>
        Books That Work<br>
        (415) 843-4402<br>
        Internet: </font><a href="mailto:bcronkhite@btw.com"><font
        size="2">bcronkhite@btw.com</font></a></p>
        <h3 align="center">Books That Work Releases 2.0 Version
        of 3D Landscape:<br>
        America's #1 Selling Landscape Design Software </h3>
        <h4 align="center"><em>Design Your Dream Landscape<br>
        and Experience It In Vivid 3D </em></h4>
        <p>PALO ALTO, Calif., March 5, 1996 -- Books That Work,
        the leading multimedia publisher of home and garden
        software, today released <i>3D Landscape 2.0</i>, the new
        version of America's #1 selling landscape design
        software. 3D Landscape 2.0 is packed with improved
        graphics, new 3D visualization capabilities, and hundreds
        of additional plants. </p>
        <p>The new 2.0 version includes: </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Enhanced 3D graphics for near photo-realistic
                views of landscape designs </li>
            <li>The ability to &quot;walk&quot; through a design
                to see it from multiple perspectives </li>
            <li>Seasonal Change to see how plants will change
                their appearance throughout the year </li>
            <li>Twice the number of plants to make the right
                choice for your design </li>
            <li>3D models of popular landscape accents, including
                gazebos, fountains, and pets </li>
        </ul>
        <p>3D Landscape 2.0 is available on CD-ROM for Windows
        3.1 and Windows 95 at retail computer and software stores
        nationwide for around $60.00. </p>
        <p><b>Visualize Your Landscape Now and in the Future</b> </p>
        <p>At anytime while you are creating a design you can see
        it in 3D with the click of a button. 3D Landscape 2.0's
        new 3D graphics engine creates incredibly vivid
        full-color three-dimensional scenes to help you evaluate
        your design. Take a virtual walk through your design to
        get a different perspective, judge proportions, and
        ensure you're pleased with the final results. The new
        Seasonal Change feature shows you how your trees and
        plants will look during different times of the year. Our
        widely-praised Growth Over Time feature demonstrates how
        the yard will look as it matures over the years so that
        you can properly plan the spacing of trees and shrubs.
        The Shadow Casting feature shows how shadows fall on your
        landscape anytime of the day or year - an important
        consideration when trying to decide where to locate a
        flower bed or a patio. </p>
        <p><b>Find the Right Plants and Accents For Your Garden </b></p>
        <p>3D Landscape 2.0 comes with an extensive database of
        more than 800 plants including trees, shrubs, and
        flowers. That means you can select the correct plants for
        your climate and setting. The expandable plant database
        lets you include your own plants in your lists. 3D
        Landscape 2.0's design engine also comes with dozens of
        landscape accent items, including everything from bird
        baths to gazebos. </p>
        <p><b>Easy from Start to Finish</b> </p>
        <p>With 3D Landscape's new Quick Start feature, you get
        sample layouts to stimulate your imagination and get you
        started quickly. As you choose the trees and plants to
        enhance your property, 3D Landscape's Shopping List
        automatically calculates the cost of your design. Print
        your 2D and 3D designs at any time to give to a
        contractor or take it with you to the nursery. </p>
        <p><b>Professional Advice At Your Fingertips</b> </p>
        <p>3D Landscape 2.0's multimedia guide book provides
        detailed explanations of landscape design principles and
        building techniques. The guide uses animations,
        photography, and audio effects to provide you with
        important information to consider when selecting plants,
        working with contractors, or trying to do-it-yourself. </p>
        <p><b>System Requirements</b> </p>
        <p>3D Landscape 2.0 requires a 486 or higher IBM PC or
        compatible, WindowsÆ 3.1 or WindowsÆ 95, 8 MB RAM, 10
        MB hard disk space, VGA graphics (256 colors), and CD-ROM
        drive (double speed or higher recommended). </p>
        <p>Books That Work, Inc., based in Palo Alto, CA, is the
        leading developer of design and visualization software
        for the home and garden. Books That Work's library of
        products include 3D Kitchen, 3D Deck, Garden
        Encyclopedia, and Home Repair Encyclopedia. To order
        products phone (800) 242-4546 or (415) 326-4280. For more
        information, contact Books That Work, 2595 E. Bayshore
        Road, Palo Alto, CA 94303. Main #(415) 326-4280 or see
        the Books That Work World Wide Web site at <a
        href="http://www.btw.com/">http://www.btw.com/</a></p>
        <p align="center"># # # </p>
