<title>Press Release - Virtual Home &amp; Garden Suite</title>
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 2.0">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<div align="center"><center>

<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="600">
    <tr>
        <td><b>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</b><table border="0">
            <tr>
                <td><font size="2"><strong>Contact:</strong><br>
                Brian Cronkhite<br>
                Public Relations Coordinator<br>
                Books That Work<br>
                (415) 843-4402<br>
                Internet: </font><a
                href="mailto:bcronkhite@btw.com"><font size="2">bcronkhite@btw.com</font></a></td>
                <td><font size="2">Julie Giacomini<br>
                Garden Escape<br>
                (415) 366-4982<br>
                Internet:</font><a href="mailto:julie@garden.com"><font
                size="2">julie@garden.com</font></a><font
                size="2"> </font></td>
            </tr>
        </table>
        <blockquote>
            <p align="center"><font size="4"><b>Books That Work
            and Garden Escape Join Forces<br>
            To Deliver Integrated Customer Solutions</b></font><br>
            <br>
            Internet and CD-ROM Technologies Create the Ultimate
            Gardener's Resource </p>
            <p align="left"><b>PALO ALTO, Calif., August 26, 1996</b>
            - Books That Work, the leading new media publisher of
            home and garden software, and Garden Escape, an
            electronic retailer and information resource for home
            gardeners on the World Wide Web, today announced the
            two companies have formed a strategic partnership to
            integrate Books That Work's content with Garden
            Escape's powerful Internet retail capabilities,
            providing customers with an enhanced resource and
            seamless shopping experience on the Web. </p>
            <p>&quot;Our goal is to provide the most
            comprehensive new media home and garden resources to
            our customers, said Dan Levin, President of Books
            That Work. &quot;Garden Escape's powerful Internet
            commerce capability adds a new and exciting dimension
            to our products by allowing the immediate online
            purchase of everything from seeds to
            fertilizer.&quot; </p>
            <p>&quot;Books That Work offers high-quality CD-ROM
            products...,&quot; said Cliff Sharples, president of
            Garden Escape. &quot;Through our joint efforts, we
            can allow customers the power to quickly and easily
            purchase products listed in...&quot; </p>
            <p>Initial efforts between the two companies will
            bring Garden Escape's specialized product catalog to
            Books That Work's Web site Gardening.com.
            Gardening.com is an Infoseek Izone, and is home to
            the Books That Work plant selector database as well
            as one of the largest collections of gardening
            related URLs on the Internet. Additionally, future
            versions of Books That Work's best-selling CD-ROM
            products, 3D Landscape and Garden Encyclopedia will
            include the capability to link to the Garden Escape
            site (garden.com) to purchase plants directly from
            the Internet. Books That Work customers will be able
            to order and purchase products at the Web site or
            through the CD-ROMs using the program's built-in Web
            browser to seamlessly connect to Garden Escape's Web
            site. The program will automatically transfer all of
            the products selected for purchase from the CD-ROM to
            Garden Escape where they will be listed and ready for
            order processing. Garden Escape will transact orders
            for all Books That Work software titles from their
            Web site at garden.com. </p>
            <p>Garden Escape delivers a combination of unique,
            high-quality products, professional advice about
            planning and designing gardens, and a broad selection
            of premium plants and garden supplies from brand-name
            suppliers. Over 5,000 products can be purchased
            exclusively online through Garden Escape for
            unmatched selection and the ultimate in convenience.
            Garden Escape employs a team of leading publishing
            experts who provide targeted editorial content,
            design ideas and inspiration. The Web site offers a
            unique customized experience for each customer,
            providing products and services to make all gardeners
            more successful as well as free access to valuable
            gardening and horticultural information. Garden
            Escape is located at http://www.garden.com. </p>
            <p><b>About the Companies</b><br>
            Books That Work, based in Palo Alto, California, is
            the leading developer of 3D design and visualization
            software for the home and garden. Books That Work
            award-winning library of products include Visual
            Home, 3D Landscape, 3D Kitchen, 3D Deck, Home
            Improvement Encyclopedia, and Garden Encyclopedia. To
            order products, phone 800-242 4546 or 415-326-4280.
            For more information, contact Books That Work, 2595
            East Bayshore Road, Palo Alto, CA 94303. Main #:
            415-326-4280. Visit the Books That Work Web site at
            http://www.btw.com. Books That Work also hosts home
            and garden communities on the Internet at
            http://homecentral.com and http://gardening.com. </p>
            <p>Garden Escape, founded in September of 1995, is an
            electronic retailer and information resource offering
            an unsurpassed collection of high-quality planting
            materials and gardening supplies. Its founders have
            extensive experience in technology, electronic
            commerce and the gardening industry. Headquartered in
            Austin, Texas, Garden Escape has offices in Northern
            California and Iowa, and is being backed by Austin
            Ventures, one of the leading venture capital firms in
            the nation. </p>
            <p align="center"># # # </p>
