<HEAD><TITLE>CSIS Publications</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="ffffff">

<a href=http://www.csis.org/cgi-bin/imagemap/button><p align="center"><IMG width=515
height=35 border=0 SRC="http://www.csis.org/images/button.gif" ISMAP></p></a>

<p align="center"><img src="http://www.csis.org/images/3pubs.gif"></p><BR>


Publications Sales Office<BR>
1800 K Street, N.W.<BR>
Washington, D.C. 20006<BR>
(202) 775-3119<BR>
<A HREF="mailto:books@csis.org">books@csis.org</A><p>
<a href="http://www.csis.org/html/faxform.html">Mail/Fax Order Form</a><P>
<p>Center experts present their analyses in a wide range of
publications.  They include
<a href="http://www.csis.org/html/pubstwq.html"><i>The Washington Quarterly</i></a>,
CSIS's scholarly journal with subscribers in more than 50 countries;
the Washington Papers; the Significant Issues Series, CSIS
Reports, and CSIS Panel Reports, which convey the findings
and policy recommendations of academics, policymakers, and
business people who gather frequently under Center auspices
to discuss current issues in international politics, economics, and security.</p><p>

In addition, the Center produces a newsletter, News@csis.dc,
and three periodicals that contain in-depth reviews of regional
trends--<A HREF="http://www.csis.org/html/2africa.html#notes">CSIS Africa Notes</A>, <a href="http://www.csis.org/html/psp.html">Post-Soviet Prospects</a>, and CSIS Policy
Papers on the Americas.  The <a href="http://www.csis.org/html/watch.html">CSIS
Watch</a> and the <A HREF="http://www.csis.org/html/alert.html">CSIS Business Alert</A> are concise analyses of breaking economic and political
issues that are faxed to public and private sector policymakers.
</p>

<p>The Center's publications are divided into the
following areas:</p>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.csis.org/html/pubsecon.html">Economics </A><BR>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.csis.org/html/pubse&e.html">Energy and the Environment</A><BR>
