<html>
<title>GIIC</title>
<body text="#000000" body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<center><img src="http://www.csis.org/images/3resear.gif"></center>
<p>
<img align=left src="http://www.csis.org/images/giiclogo.gif"><center><br>
<h2>Global Information<br>
Infrastructure Commission</h2><BR></center>
<p>
<hr>
<p>
As the markets and applications for information technologies and services move beyond the limits of traditional institutions, resources, and geography, new frictions as well as new opportunities arise.  Little is understood about how these will evolve in a global context.  What was once the sole purview of government communications ministries (PTTs) and tidy monopolies in many countries is now shifting to private ownership and competitive forces.  This calls for new constructs for cooperation, coordination, and
leadership that cannot be met by governmental bodies, trade associations, or industry alliances.
<p>
The Global Information Infrastructure Commission was established in the summer of 1995 to meet this need.  The purpose of the GIIC is to promote private sector leadership and transnational cooperation in information infrastructure development.  Its goals are to advance economic growth, education, and quality of life in both developing and developed countries and to involve private and public sector leaders from a diversity of countries, industries, organizations, and fields of expertise.<p>
The GIIC's objectives are fourfold:
<ul>
<li>to provide a framework for marshaling private sector leadership in cooperation with governments;</li>
<li>to facilitate initiatives, research, and recommendations involving developing as well as industrialized countries;</li>
<li>to promote applications and demonstration projects in support of key areas such as education, health care, and the environment; and</li>
<li>strengthen the links and cooperation between various national information infrastructure task forces and industry initiatives.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong><a href="http://www.gii.org/giic">The GIIC has its own Home Page!</A>
Please visit this extensive web site for more information about the GIIC and its activities.</strong>
