<p align="center"><img src="http://www.csis.org/images/3pubs.gif"></p>
<h1>The Washington Quarterly</h1><hr>
The purview of 
<i>The Washington Quarterly</i> is broad, ranging across the full set of political,
economics, and security issues related to the international engagement of the United States.
 But its focus is policy and the way in which analysis of international events must be translated
into policy choices and actions.  Its contributors are professionally, politically, and geographically
diverse.  TWQ has subscribers in more than 50 countries and is available in bookstores and
on newstands.<p>

<A HREF="http://mitpress.mit.edu/jrnls-catalog/washington.html">For more on
the <I>Washington Quarterly</I></A><P>

