<head><title>What is CSIS?</title>
</head>

<body bgcolor="#ffffff"><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<p align="center"><img src="/images/3missio.gif"></p>
<h1>What is CSIS?</h1>



 <p>    The Center for Strategic and International Studies (CSIS) 
is a
     public policy research institution dedicated to policy 
analysis and
     impact.  CSIS is the only institution of its kind that 
maintains
     resident experts on all the world's major geographical 
regions.  It
     also covers key functional areas, such as international 
finance,
     the emerging markets, U.S. domestic and economic policy 
related
     to the Strengthening of America, and U.S. foreign policy and
     national security issues. </p> 

    <p> For more than three decades, the "strategic" approach of 
CSIS
     has emphasized long-range, anticipatory, and integrated 
thinking
     on a wide range of policy issues.  </p>

     <p>This approach is now more important than ever.  The end of 



the
     Cold War--while eliminating the danger of apocalypse--has
     ushered in accelerated change, new forces, increased
     complexities, shorter time frames for decisionmaking, and
     unprecedented challenges to leaders worldwide.</p>

<p>     The Center's <a href="http://www.csis.org/html/research.html">staff
</a>, consisting of 80 research specialists, 



80
     support staff, and 70 interns, is committed to generating 
strategic
     analysis on this "New World Disorder" by analyzing policy
     options, exploring contingencies, and making recommendations.
</p>

<p>     Founded in 1962 and located in Washington, D.C., CSIS is a
     private, tax-exempt institution.  Its <a 
href="http://www.csis.org/html/research.html">research</a> is 
non-partisan and
     non-proprietary.</p>

<p>     The Center's 1994 budget of $15 million was supported by
     contributions from corporations and individuals worldwide,
     foundation grants, non-classified contracts with the U.S.
     government, and revenue from its $15 million endowment.  To
     achieve longer-term financial security, the Center has 
launched a
     $60 million endowment campaign to build on its existing
     endowment of $15 million.</p>

<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.csis.org/html/mission2.html">What is the mission of CSIS?</a>





<LI><A href="http://www.csis.org/html/mission3.html">How does CSIS implement this 
vision?</A>

<LI><A href="http://www.csis.org/html/mission4.html">What are
CSIS values?  What does it believe? </A>

<LI><A href="http://www.csis.org/html/mission5.html">What constituencies
does CSIS serve? </A>

<LI><A href="http://www.csis.org/html/mission6.html">What
criteria does CSIS have for selecting
projects? </A></UL>



