<body bgcolor=#ffffff>

<p align="center"><img src="http://www.csis.org/images/3missio.gif"></p>
<h1>What criteria does CSIS have for selecting projects?</h1>

     CSIS uses the following criteria when it decides whether or 
not to proceed with a new 
project:

<blockquote><p>Is it strategic?  Of pivotal importance?  
Anticipatory and forward-looking?</p>

<p>Does CSIS have a comparative advantage--substantive expertise 
and organizational 
strength--to exploit?</p>

<p>What kind of results, or product, will it generate?  Will the 
project have an impact on 
policy?  Will it change things for the better?  </p>

<p>Can multiplier effects be realized through CSIS research and 
its network?</p>

<p>Can the project be funded, and/or has a lead donor been 
identified?  Is it financially 
viable?  How long will it last?  When will it be sunsetted?</p>
</blockquote>

<UL>
<LI><A href="http://www.csis.org/html/mission1.html">What is CSIS? </A>

<li><a href="http://www.csis.org/html/mission2.html">What is the mission of CSIS?</a>



<LI><A href="http://www.csis.org/html/mission3.html">How does CSIS implement this 
vision?</A>

<LI><A href="http://www.csis.org/html/mission4.html">What are
CSIS values?  What does it believe? </A>

<LI><A href="http://www.csis.org/html/mission5.html">What constituencies
does CSIS serve? </A>

<LI><A href="http://www.csis.org/html/mission6.html">What
criteria does CSIS have for selecting
projects? </A></UL>




