<a href="#turkey">Turkey:</a> The Challenge of a New Role<p>
</font>
</td>


<td valign=top>

<h3><a name="france">Does France Still Count?  The French Role in the New Europe</a></h3> 
Steven Philip Kramer<p>
<i>Washington Papers/Praeger	113 pp. 	1994<br>
ISBN 0-275-95061-1 (pb)	$12.95<br>
0-275-95060-3 (hb) 	$45.00</i>


<p><hr><p>
<h3><a name="ethnic">Ethnic Politics in Eastern Europe:
A Guide to Nationality Policies, Organizations, and Parties</a></h3>
Janusz Bugajski<p>

"Bugajski presents the background necessary to understand relations between the various ethnic groups in the region in a very concise manner. . . .[His] ability to condense the complex series of recent events in the former Yugoslavia while effectively presenting the view from each republic deserves particular praise." - Nationalities Papers<p>
<i>Copublished Book/M.E. Sharpe	493 pp. 	1994<br>
ISBN 1-56324-282-6 (hb) 	$75.00<br>
	1-56324-283-4 (pb) 	$34.95
</i>

<p><hr><p>

<h3><a name="transatl">Making Transatlantic Defense Cooperation Work</a></h3>
<b>Findings and Recommendations of the CSIS Atlantic Partnership Project</b><p>
The Rt. Hon. Sir Geoffrey Pattie, MP, and Michael T. Smith, cochairs<br>
<a href="http://www.csis.org/html/4goure.html">Daniel GourÈ</a>, Robin Niblett, and <a href="http://www.csis.org/html/4earnest.html">David Earnest</a>, research staff<p>
This report recommends legislative and regulatory approaches to strengthening cooperation between U.S. and European defense industries. The project's findings, formulated by a steering committee of 15 leading U.S. and European defense CEOs and corporate leaders, suggest to governments on both sides of the Atlantic ways to provide defense industries with new incentives to collaborate on the development and production of next-generation military technologies and systems.<p>
<i>Panel Report	45 pp.	1996<br>
ISBN 0-89206-286-X		$14.95</i>

<p><hr><p>

<h3><a name="migration">Migration and the New Europe</a></h3>
Kimberly A. Hamilton, editor<br>
Contributors: <a href="http://www.csis.org/html/4fauriol.html">Georges A. Fauriol</a>, Robert E. Hunter, Soren Jessen-Petersen, Kathleen Newland, Demetrios G. Papademetriou, Sebastiano Vincelli, <a href="http://www.csis.org/html/4weintra.html">Sidney Weintraub</a>, Jonas Widgren<p>
S<i>ignificant Issues Series	115 pp.	1994<br>
ISBN 0-89206-214-2		$16.00</i>

<p><hr><p>


<h3><a name="nordic">Nordic-Baltic Security:
An International Perspective</a></h3>
Arne Olav Brundtland and Don M. Snider, editors<br>
Contributors: Clive Archer, <a href="http://www.csis.org/html/4cambone.html">Stephen A. Cambone</a>, Helmut Hubel, Atis Lejins, Sergei Oznobistchev, Trivimi Velliste<p>
<i>Panel Report	132 pp. 	1994<br>
ISBN 0-89206-256-8 		$16.95
</i>

<p><hr><p>

<h3><a name="unity">Stay the Course: European Unity and Atlantic Solidarity</a></h3>
<a href="http://www.csis.org/html/4serfaty.html">Simon Serfaty</a><p>
The policies of the United States toward Europe have been among the most consistent, successful, and rewarding of the post-World War II period. To abandon Europe would be to ignore those policies' achievements_affluence, stability, and security_at huge cost to the interests of the United States. In the remaining years of this decade, Europe's fate will be determined by decisions that are yet to be made but can no longer be postponed. The United States is not being invited to preserve the status quo, but to enforce policies that respond to dual requirements -- transatlantic solidarity and European unity. The issues raised by the author -- from the instability of financial systems to information warfare and "virtual security" -- are both far-ranging and complete.<p>
<i>Washington Papers/Praeger  c. 160 pp.	Forthcoming <br>
ISBN 0-275-95933-3 (pb)	$16.95 Est.<br>
          0-275-95932-5 (hb)	$52.95 Est.</i>

<p><hr><p>


<h3><a name="turkey">Turkey: The Challenge of a New Role</a></h3>
Andrew Mango<p>
"This book is a tour de force and tour d'horizon of modern Turkey by an old Turkish hand. In nine compact chapters the author manages to summarize succinctly the major political, economic, social, and diplomatic developments the country has confronted in the last two decades and the challenges it faces in the final decade of the 20th century. The major focus is on policies to enhance modernizing and developing an export oriented economy." - CHOICE<p>
<i>Washington Papers/Praeger	144 pp. 	1994<br>
ISBN	0-275-94986-9 (pb) 	$12.95<br>
	0-275-94985-0 (hb) 	$45.00</i>

<p>


</td></tr></table>

