<H1>CSIS Calendar of Events</H1>

<H3>January-February 1997</H3>

	All events are in Washington, D.C. and by invitation only unless otherwise indicated.  To request an invitation or additional information, please contact the person listed for the event.<BR>
<B>[BIO = By Invitation Only]</B><P><HR><P>



<b>Jan. 10-Jan. 13</b>		<b><i>Restructuring the U.S.-Japan Security Relationship</i></b><br>
		The Pacific Forum CSIS is cosponsoring a bilateral conference in Tokyo 			with the Okazaki Institute and the Policy Study Group in a final meeting of 			a two year project that focuses on ways to strengthen and adapt the 			alliance for the post-Cold War environment.  A public conference will be 			held on January 13 to disseminate the group's deliberations and a final 			publication of background papers and conference discussions on U.S. and 			Japanese views will be released.<br>
