<h3><a name="aids">Global HIV/AIDS: A Strategy for U.S. Leadership</a></h3>
<b>A Consensus Report of the CSIS Working Group on Global HIV/AIDS</b><p>

As the world becomes increasingly interconnected through trade and commerce, infectious diseases pose threats that spread beyond national borders.  Without a "magic cure" in sight, action is needed to prevent the spread of the deadly HIV/AIDS virus.  This study outlines a broad agenda for policymakers, public health officials, and leaders of nongovernmental organizations.  The message is clear: deterring the spread of the pandemic is a global challenge, requiring a global strategic response.  As a world leader, the United States has a clear strategic interest in committing itself to this effort.<p>

"This is an excellent report and one that should be on the desk of every leader in the world." - AIDS Book Review Journal<p>
<i>Panel Report	63 pp. 	1994<br>
ISBN 0-89206-254-1 		$19.95</i>

<p><hr><p>


<h3><a name="reform">Health Care Reform: Ensuring Quality at an Affordable Price</a></h3>
Alexander T. Hunt, editor<br>
Contributors: Grace-Marie Arnett,
Douglas L. Cocks, Tyler G. Hughes,
Frank J. Weaver<p>
This report summarizes the proceedings of a forum held in August 1994 in Dallas, Texas, cosponsored by CSIS and Representative Dick Armey (R-Tex.). The forum focused on the tax treatment of health insurance, the measurement of the quality of health care, and the importance of sustaining biomedical innovation.<p>
<i>CSIS Report	35 pp. 	1995<br>
ISBN 0-89206-313-0 		$9.95</i>

<p><hr><p>

<h3><a name="wyoming">Integrated Systems in Frontier Health Care Delivery: The Unique Needs of Wyoming</a></h3>
Sheryl R. Fox and Alexander T. Hunt, editors<br>
Contributors: Betsey S. Blakeslee, Richard W. Johnson, Jr., Robert Charles Kidd II, Thomas Pringle, Steven Rosenberg, Alan K. Simpson<p>
This report provides a summary of the proceedings of a forum on Frontier Health Care Delivery, cosponsored by CSIS and Senator Alan Simpson (R-Wyo.).  The forum brought together local and national experts to discuss the special challenges of delivering health care in Wyoming, particularly the difficulties of meeting the demand for physicians and medical facilities in sparsely populated areas. <p>
<i>CSIS Report	39 pp.	1995<br>
ISBN 0-89206-304-1 		$9.95</i>

<p><hr><p>

<h3><a name="migration">Migration and the New Europe</a></h3>
Kimberly A. Hamilton, editor<br>
Contributors: <a href="http://www.csis.org/html/4fauriol.html">Georges A. Fauriol</a>, Robert E. Hunter, Soren Jessen-Petersen, Kathleen Newland, Demetrios G. Papademetriou, Sebastiano Vincelli, <a href="http://www.csis.org/html/4weintra.html">Sidney Weintraub</a>, Jonas Widgren<p>
<i>Significant Issues Series	115 pp.	1994<br>
ISBN 0-89206-214-2		$16.00</i>

