<h3><a name="pop">Population and U.S. National Interests: A Framework for Thinking about the Connections</a></h3>
<b>A Report of the CSIS Steering 
Committee on Population  and U.S. National Interests </b><p>
Senator Alan K. Simpson and Representative Anthony C. Beilenson, cochairs<br>
<a href="http://www.csis.org/html/4wendt.html">David Wendt</a> and Alene Gelbard, project directors<br>
Alex deSherbinin and Karen Levy, project co-coordinators<p>
This "framework for thinking" about issues of demographics and U.S. national interests is the result of a one-year process guided by a steering committee, cochaired by Representative Anthony Beilenson (D-Calif.) and Senator Alan Simpson (R-Wyo.).  It describes a number of issues and areas in which sophisticated thinking about connections between population and U.S. foreign policy is necessary and offers salient policy prescriptions to address the challenges of global population growth.<p>
<i>Panel Report 	34 pp.	1996<br>
ISBN 0-89206-278-9 		$14.95</i>

