<head><title> How does CSIS implement this vision? </title>
</head>

<body bgcolor=#ffffff>
<p align="center"><img src="http://www.csis.org/images/3missio.gif"></p>
<h1>How does CSIS implement this vision?
</h1>

    CSIS achieves this mission in three ways:
<UL>

<LI>      <b>By Generating Strategic Analysis:</b>  CSIS is
<i>a source of scholarly analysis
</i> on international public policy issues.  On the one hand, it 
covers the world with 
real-time assessments.  On the other, it provides long-term 
analysis based on understanding of 
underlying forces and trends, utilizing alternative scenarios to 
reflect various contingencies. 
 This dual approach both guides the immediate policymaking process 

and alerts decision-makers 
to future policy challenges and options.<BR><BR>

<LI>       <b>By Convening Policymakers and other Influential 
Parties:</b>  CSIS has a 
longstanding reputation for bringing together 
<i>the right people on the right issues, breaking 
stalemates, and pushing debate forward </i>in a non-partisan 
environment.  It attracts leaders 
from government, the private sector, and academia from around the 
world.<BR><BR>

<LI>        <b>By Building Structures for Policy Action:</b>  CSIS
<i>mobilizes government and private-sector leaders in action 
commissions and other high-level groups, and then moves 
relevant policymakers to take concrete action.</i>  These 
initiatives are designed to achieve 
specific, well-defined results--such as replacing the current 
anti-savings, anti-investment tax 
code in the United States, or increasing foreign investment flows 
to economies in transition. 
</ul>

<p>Specifically, CSIS action commissions and other high-level 
groups have been formed in Poland, 
St. Petersburg, Ukraine, the South American Southern Cone, 
Singapore, and Turkey to explore 
concrete ways of expanding economic, financial, and political ties 

with the United States.  At 
home, CSIS has had an important policy impact on fiscal, tax, 
health care, and capital market 
reform as a result of its Strengthening of American Commission and 

its follow-up effort, The 
National 
Campaign to Strengthen America.</p>

<UL>
<LI><A href="http://www.csis.org/html/mission1.html">What is CSIS? </A>

<li><a href="http://www.csis.org/html/mission2.html">What is the mission of CSIS?</a>



<LI><A href="http://www.csis.org/html/mission3.html">How does CSIS implement this 
vision?</A>

<LI><A href="http://www.csis.org/html/mission4.html">What are
CSIS values?  What does it believe? </A>

<LI><A href="http://www.csis.org/html/mission5.html">What constituencies
does CSIS serve? </A>

<LI><A href="http://www.csis.org/html/mission6.html">What
criteria does CSIS have for selecting
projects? </A></UL>
