<title>ICS Team</title>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<center><img src="http://www.csis.org/images/3scholar.gif"></center>
<p>
<h2>ICS Team</h2>
<p>
<hr>
<p>
<a href="http://www.csis.org/html/4dougan.html">Ambassador Diana Lady Dougan</a> is Chair of the ICS Program and CSIS Senior Adviser. She has served in senior communications, foreign policy, and management positions for more than three decades. Ambassador Dougan has been honored by appointments by both Republican and Democratic presidents in Senate-confirmed positions, including six years overseeing international communications policy for the U.S. government. Early in her career she was the first CATV Marketing Director for Time Inc. The ICS Program Director, <a href="http://www.csis.org/html/4garriso.html">William B. Garrison, Jr.</a>, has held telecommunications policy posts in both state and national government and has over 15 years experience in the private sector as President of the Telecommunications Consulting Group, Inc., where he specialized in comparative industry structure and international market and regulatory dynamics.
<p>
Senior Associate <a href="http://www.csis.org/html/4dizard.html">Wilson Dizard</a> is a widely published author on the electronic media, international satellite development, and international telecoms and information policy. Senior Associate <a href="http://www.csis.org/html/4pipe.html">G. Russell Pipe</a> is one of the foremost international experts on telecom trade and services issues. As publisher of Transnational Data Report (now I-Ways), he developed the first publication forum for information service policy issues. He has worked extensively as adviser to the ITU, OECD, UNDP, and other intergovernmental organizations as well as to leading international corporations. <a href="http://www.csis.org/html/4fan.html">Fan Xing</a>, ICS Asia Telecom Research Fellow, has recently completed a visiting fellowship at Harvard. His upcoming book on China telecommunications draws from his experience in teaching management in China as well as working in the Chinese Ministry of Post and Telecommunications.
<p>
Project coordinator Ann Marie Stark and administrative/publications specialists Jonathan Hoffman and Christopher Foss form the ICS support infrastructure, each bringing their own special skills and talents to help maintain the Program's high level of excellence, outreach, and innovation.
<p>
