<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE> B'Tselem, Press Release - November 19, 1996 </TITLE>
</HEAD>
                                       
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=+3><I> Press Release - November 19, 1996 </I></FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=+2><B> Beatings and Degredation of Palestinians: <BR>
Routine Rather than Unusual Occurrences </B></FONT><BR>
</CENTER>
<HR>
<P>
 
<FONT SIZE=+2><B>B'</B></FONT>Tselem maintains that the beatings of Palestinians by Border Police
officers broadcast last night on the Israeli evening news are unique only in
that a photographer was present at the scene and filmed the incident.
<P>
Beatings and degradation of Palestinians by Police and Border Police are
common. In B'Tselem's report published in September, "Beatings, Maltreatment
and Degradation of Palestinians by Police during June-July, 1996," ten such
incidents were described, and they are only a sample from the large number
of similar cases about which human rights organizations are aware. The
characterization  by Israeli officials of these incidents as "exceptions" is
only an attempt to minimize a serious and troublesome situation about which
B'Tselem and other human rights organizations have repeatedly warned.
<P>
The B'Tselem report also refutes the contention that the recent beatings are
a response to the events of  September, as the B'Tselem report deals with
events that occurred in June and July.
<P>
Both in the incident which was photographed and in over half of the cases in
B'Tselem's report, Palestinians who enter Israel without permits are beaten
and sent back to the Occupied Territories without being prosecuted.  This
raises the suspicion that there is an unwritten policy of using violence and
humiliation rather than prosecution of the offenders. In any event, the
authorities have clearly adopted a policy to disregard this widespread
phenomenon.
<P>
B'Tselem urges the Israeli government to end, once and for all, the policy
of violence against Palestinians, whether this policy is implemented with
the authorities' formal approval or by their utter disregard of its existence.


<P>
<HR>
<TABLE WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD ALIGN=center VALIGN=middle WIDTH=50% BGCOLOR="Lime"><A HREF="index.htm"> Back to Recent Press Releases </A></TD>
