<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE> B'Tselem, Newspaper Advertisement  - November 5, 1996 </TITLE>
</HEAD>
                                       
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=+3><I> Newspaper Advertisement - November 5, 1996 </I></FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=+2><B> On the Prohibition on Settling in Occupied Territory </B></FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE=+1><NOBR>
The following is the <B>third</B> in a series of paid advertisements 
<WBR> published by B'Tselem in the Hebrew dailies, <I>Ha'aretz</I> and <I>Yediot Aharonot </I></NOBR></FONT>
</CENTER>
<HR>
<P>
 
Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, in his speech to the United States Congress: 

<BLOCKQUOTE><FONT COLOR=red>
"The time has come for countries in the Middle East to place human rights
and democracy on their agendas."</FONT> 
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>

     
<FONT SIZE=+1><B>                         
The Facts:
</B></FONT>
<UL>
<LI>    Israel has expropriated hundreds of thousands of square
     kilometers from Palestinians in the Occupied Territories and
     established on them permanent civilian settlements of Jewish
     Israeli citizens to alter the demography and create political
     facts on the ground.
<P>
<LI>    International conventions prohibit an occupier from
     transferring persons from its territory to the occupied
     territory and from taking any action not intended for military
     needs or to benefit the local population.
<P>
<LI>    Israel prevented development of Palestinian towns and villages
     and Palestinian agriculture and hampered their chances for
     self-determination. It created a situation in which two
     populations living in the same area are subject to different
     systems of law and separate infrastructures; one population
     (the settlers) is granted widescale benefits, and the other
     population (the Palestinians) is denied basic rights and
     restricted in innumerable ways.
<P>
<LI>    Most of the settlers did not violate Israel's laws when they
     settled in the Occupied Territories; it was Israeli governments
     that violated international law by promoting settlements and
     offering incentives to populate them.
</UL>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B>
The Questions:
</B></FONT>
<P>
Aren't the settlements needed for security? Not at all:
<UL>
<LI>    During implementation of the interim agreements, Israel closed
     many military bases in the Gaza Strip and throughout the West
     Bank. However, it did not evacuate one settlement even in
     cases where it was particularly difficult to defend the
     settlers. 
<P>
<LI>    The settlements intended to protect us are protected by large
     numbers of security forces, thousands of kilometers of
     additional land have been expropriated to pave bypass roads
     at a cost of hundreds of millions of shekels, and now the
     IDF is allocating forces to protect these roads that protect
     the settlements that are intended to protect us. There is
     no end to it.
<P>
<LI>    The settlements delay and complicate security and civil
     arrangements in the Occupied Territories. Hebron is only one
     small example of this major problem.
</UL>
Why are Jews prohibited from settling in all of the Land of Israel?
<UL>

<LI>    The prohibition on settlement is not based on nationality
     or race, but rather is intended to prevent "colonization"
     of the occupied territory. Israel may administer the area
     temporarily, but it may not make permanent changes, certainly
     not by establishing settlements for its citizens, and not
     by unilateral action.
</UL>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B>
The Conclusions:
</B></FONT>
<UL>
<LI>    Israel must immediately cease expropriating land, enlarging
     settlements, establishing new settlements, and paving bypass
     roads.
<P>
<LI>    Settlers' human rights must not be violated.  If it is ultimately
     agreed to evacuate them, Israel must ensure their housing,
     sources of income, education for their children, etc.
     Alternatively, if it is agreed that the settlers will remain
     in the territories, they must reside there as citizens with
     equal rights under the authority or state in which they will
     be located.
</UL>
  


<P>
<CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=+3 COLOR=red><B>
HUMAN RIGHTS MUST BE RESPECTED!
</B></FONT> 

<P>
<HR>
