<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE> B'Tselem, Joint Press Release - September 28, 1996 </TITLE>
</HEAD>
                                       
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=+3><I> Joint Press Release - September 28, 1996 </I></FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=+2><B> "THE WRITING WAS ON THE WALL" </B></FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B>
a joint release by Israeli human rights organizations
</B></FONT>
</CENTER>
<HR>
<P>
 
<FONT SIZE=+2><B>T</B></FONT>
he undersigned human rights organizations are shocked and
saddened by the loss of life during the events of the past few
days, and we express our condolences to the bereaved families,
Israeli and Palestinian.
<P>
The opening of the tunnel in East Jerusalem is not the only cause
of these events; they broke out after frustration and bitterness
had built up among Palestinians as a result of Israeli actions in
the Occupied Territories over the years: closure, demolition of
houses, establishment and expansion of Jewish settlements,
massive administrative detentions, and use of torture. These
measures have led to Palestinians being unable to make a living,
restrictions on their freedom of movement, expropriation of their
land, and dependence of Palestinians on an infinite number of
"security permits."
<P>
We have repeatedly warned, and we warn once again, that violation
of human rights does not improve security, but rather is likely
to backfire and drive frustrated Palestinians to violence against
Israel. The recent events are tragic proof of the validity of
these forecasts.
<P>
These comments are not intended to justify any act of violence by
any party. We condemn the arbitrary use of force and attacks on
innocent persons on both sides. Rather, we make these comments to
indicate again the pressing and vital need to respect human
rights.
<P>


<CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=+2><B>
WITHOUT RESPECT FOR HUMAN RIGHTS<BR>
NEITHER PEACE NOR SECURITY IS POSSIBLE
</B></FONT>
</CENTER>
<P>
Israeli human rights organizations urge the Israeli government
and the Palestinian Authority to:
<UL>
<LI>    act with restraint against demonstrators, and restrict the
use of firearms to life-threatening situations;
<P>
<LI>    investigate thoroughly the circumstances of the deaths that
occurred during the recent violence.
</UL>
We also urge the Israeli government to:
<UL>
<LI>    allow Palestinians freedom of movement throughout the
Occupied Territories;
<P>
<LI>    permit medical personnel to move freely throughout the
Occupied Territories at all times and in all situations;
<P>
<LI>    ensure sources of income for tens of thousands of
Palestinian workers who lost their income following the
closure, and enable operation of a properly functioning
economy;
<P>
<LI>    refrain from collective or extra-judicial punishment;
<P>
<LI>    respect the basic rights of detainees, and refrain from
arbitrary detention;
<P>
<LI>    release administrative detainees or bring them to trial ;
<P>
<LI>    cease expropriating land to build and expand Jewish
settlements, and refrain from demolishing houses; and
<P>
<LI>    refrain from deporting Palestinians from the Occupied
Territories.
</UL>

<CENTER>
<HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=center>
</CENTER>
<P>
<B>B'Tselem</B> - The Israeli Information Center for Human Rights in the
Occupied Territories
<P>
<B>DCI</B> - The International Association for Children's Rights
<P>
<B>HaMoked: Center for the Defense of the Individual</B>
<P>
<B>Physicians for Human Rights</B>
<P>
<B>The Public Committee against Torture in Israel</B>
<P>
<B>Shomrey Mishpat</B> - Rabbis for Human Rights

<P>
<HR>
