<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE> B'Tselem, Press Release - April 1996 </TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=+3><B><I> Press Release - April 1996 </I></B></FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=+2><B>
Monthly Report
</B></FONT>
</CENTER>
<HR>
<P>
<B>According to B'Tselem's data, during April 1996:</B>
<P>
One Israeli civilian who was injured by a Palestinian inside the
green line on February, died of his wounds.
<P>
According to the Associated Press no Palestinians suspected of
collaborating with the Israeli authorities were killed this month
by Palestinians. According to the IDF Spokesperson's Office one
Palestinian suspected of collaborating with the Israeli authorities
was killed during this month by Palestinians.
<P><CENTER>
<HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=center>
</CENTER>
<P>
<B>From the Beginning of the Intifada Until the End of April 1996:</B>
<P>
<U>In the Territories:</U>
<P>
1249 Palestinian residents of the Occupied Territories have been
killed by Israeli security forces. Of these:
<UL>                       
<LI> Shooting deaths (including plastic and "rubber" bullets)  1212
<LI> Non-shooting deaths  (beatings, burns and other)            37
</UL>
262 Children were killed, of these: 
<UL>
<LI>     aged 12 and younger    68
<LI>     aged 13 to 16         194
</UL>
An additional 103 Palestinians were killed by Israeli civilians
and 28 by collaborators.
<P>
76 Israeli civilians, including three infants; 68 members of the
Israeli security forces; and three foreigners were killed by
Palestinians.
<P>
Five Palestinian policemen were killed by Israeli security forces.
One lsraeli civilian and One member of the Israeli security forces
were killed by the Palestinian Police.
<P>
According to the Associated Press, 830 Palestinians suspected of
collaborating with the Israeli authorities have been killed in
the Occupied Territories by Palestinians, whereas according to
the IDF Spokesperson's Office, 1012 Palestinians suspected of
collaborating with the Israeli authorities were killed by
Palestinians (this number does not include 47 Palestinians killed
by Palestinians in detention facilities.) 
<P>                                            

<U>Within the Green Line: </U>
<P>
144 Israeli civilians, 17 foreigners, and 56 members of the Israeli
security forces were killed by Palestinian residents of the Occupied
Territories. 
<P>
28 Palestinians from the Territories were killed within the Green
Line by the Israeli security forces, and 23 were killed  by Israeli
civilians.
<CENTER>
<HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=center>
</CENTER>
<P>
<B>From September 14 1993, following the Signing of the Oslo Accord
until the End of April 1996:</B>
<P>

<U>In the Territories:</U>
<P>
178 Palestinians were killed by Israeli security forces, 24 of
them children age 16 and under (three were under the age of 12).
<P>
49 Palestinians were killed by Israeli civilians and three were
killed by collaborators.
<P>
28 Israeli civilians, one foreigner, and 26 security forces members
were killed by Palestinians. 
<P>
Five Palestinian police officers were killed by Israeli security
forces. One Israeli civilian and one security force member were
killed by the Palestinian Police.
<P>

<U>Within the Green Line: </U>
<P>
90 Israeli civilians, 13 foreigners and 39 members of the security
forces were killed by Palestinian residents of the Territories.
11 Palestinians were killed by security forces and two Palestinians
were killed by Israeli civilians.
<P>
<CENTER>
<HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=center>
</CENTER>
<B>From May 5 1994, following the Signing of the Cairo Accord, until
the End of April 1996:</B>
<P>
<U>In the Occupied Territories:</U>
<P>
71 Palestinians were killed by Israeli security forces, including
seven children age 16 and under.
<P>
Seven Palestinians were killed by Israeli civilians and three were
killed by collaborators.
<P>
12 Israeli civilians, one foreigner and 22 members of the Israeli
security forces were killed by Palestinians.
<P>
Five Palestinian police officers were killed by Israeli security
forces.  One Israeli civilian and one member of the Israeli security
forces were killed by the Palestinian Police.
<P>
<U>Within the Green Line:</U>
<P>
67 Israeli civilians, 13 foreigners and 35 members of the security
forces were killed by Palestinian residents of the Occupied
Territories. Six Palestinians were killed by Israeli security forces
and one Palestinian was killed by Israeli civilians.
<P>
<CENTER>
<HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=center>
</CENTER>
<B>Notes:</B>
<OL>
<LI>   West Bank figures include East Jerusalem.
<LI>   Revision of the running totals which result in apparent 
     discrepancies between this month's data and those of previous
     months are a result of ongoing research, which occasionally
     yields new information regarding past events.
<LI>   The figures of the IDF Spokesperson's Office concerning
     Palestinians who were killed by Palestinians do not include
     those who were killed in the areas in which security
     responsibilities have been transferred to the Palestinian
     Authority. 
</UL>
<P>
