<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE> B'Tselem, Press Release - February 18, 1996 </TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=+3><B><I> Press Release - February 18, 1996 </I></B></FONT>
</CENTER>
<HR>
<I>
Israeli human rights organizations - the Israel Section of Defense
of Children International, B'Tselem, The Public Committee Against
Torture in Israel, HaMoked: Center for the Defense of the Individual,
and the Association of Physicians for Human Rights: Demand that the 
IDF and the Police conduct an investigation into the murder of 
prisoners in Israeli prison facilities.
</I>
<HR>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=+2><B>H</B></FONT>uman rights organizations express profound outrage at the most
recent death of a Palestinian prisoner in an IDF prison facility.
<P>
'Adel Yusuf Ash'hatit, 21 years old from Dura in the Hebron District,
died in the Megiddo military prison, apparently on Thursday, February
15, 1996.  Media reports indicate that prisoners with whom Ash'hatit
was held are suspected in his death.
<P>
This is the second recent death at Megiddo prison.  On February
1 of this year, 'Abd a-Rahman 'Omar Salim Zid Kilani, 21 years
old from Ya'bed was murdered.  Prior to these two deaths, four
Palestinian prisoners died similar deaths in the Ketziot military
detention facility.
<P>
As stated above, these deaths took place in Israeli military
detention facilities, located inside Israel.  Therefore, the wardens
of these facilities bear sole responsibility for ensuring the safety
and well-being of the prisoners, according to Israeli law.
<P>
Section 322 of the Israeli Penal Code 5737-1977, entitled
"Responsibility for the Helpless" states: "Whosoever bears
responsibility for a person who, because of his age . . . detention
or any other reason, cannot divest himself of that responsibility
and cannot provide life's necessities for himself or provide for
his health needs . . . it is incumbent upon him to provide his
requirements for sustenance, to take care of his health, and to
consider him as one who has caused results concerning the person's
life or health because he did not fulfill his said obligation."
<P>
We demand that the prison wardens and those responsible within
the IDF immediately take the steps necessary to prevent the
occurrence of additional such incidents.  In addition, we demand
that Military Police Investigations and the Israel Police investigate
these incidents of death, in light of the details stated above,
in order to identify those suspected of causing the deaths and
those who bear responsibility for them.
<P>
We also call upon Palestinian organizations to work to end these
phenomenon.
<P>
<HR>
<TABLE WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD ALIGN=center VALIGN=middle WIDTH=50% BGCOLOR="Lime"><A HREF="index.htm"> Back to Recent Press Releases </A></TD>
<TD ALIGN=center VALIGN=middle WIDTH=50% BGCOLOR="Aqua"><A HREF="../index.htm"> Back to B'Tselem homepage </A></TD>
</TR>
