<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE> B'Tselem, Press Release - January 3, 1996 </TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=+3><B><I> Press Release - January 3, 1996 </I></B></FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=+2><B>
B'Tselem Fieldworker Bassem 'Eid Released From His Detention in Ramallah
</B></FONT>
</CENTER>
<HR>

<FONT SIZE=+2><B>I</B></FONT>n spite of the denials of officials within the Palestinian
Authority that B'Tselem Fieldworker Bassem 'Eid was being
detained and held by the PA, 'Eid was released this evening
from detention by the Authority in Ramallah.
<P>
'Eid was held for 24 hours.  He was not interrogated nor was
he told the reason for his detention.  Throughout this period,
officials of the Authority denied the fact that he was
detained and claimed that he was not being held by any of the
Palestinian security forces.
<P>
'Eid's detention is a blatant example of an increasingly
prevalent pattern in which the Palestinian Authority silences
and discourages anyone who voices public criticism rather than
address the substance of the criticism.  Equally serious is
the denials which, in this case, are intended to generate
uncertainty and to increase the concern for 'Eid's well-being.
<P>
<HR>
