<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE> B'Tselem, Press Release - January 3, 1995 </TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=+3><B><I> Press Release - January 3, 1995 </I></B></FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=+2><B>
B'Tselem Fieldworker, Bassem 'Eid, Detained by Palestinian Police
</B></FONT>
</CENTER>
<HR>

<FONT SIZE=+2><B>Y</B></FONT>esterday at 11 p.m., a Palestinian police officer came to the
home of B'Tselem fieldworker Bassem 'Eid and requested 'Eid to
accompany him to Ramallah for questioning. 
<P>
This morning 'Eid notified B'Tselem that he is being detained in
Ramallah at the headquarters of "Force 17". He added that he has
not yet been interrogated and has not been told the reason for
his detention. A strong suspicion exists that 'Eid was arrested
because of the harsh criticism he has voiced in his work at B'Tselem
and for the international human rights organization Reporters sans
Frontieres concerning actions of the Palestinian Authority.
<P>
'Eid was one of the authors of a report B'Tselem published in August,
1995 dealing with human rights violations by the Preventive Security
Service of the Palestinian Authority. In responding to the report,
Gibril Rajoub, head of the PSS, proclaimed that 'Eid is "an Israeli
agent."
<P>
Recently 'Eid has followed the matter of the detention of the editor
of Al-Quds, Maher 'Al-Alami, by the PSS.
<P>
B'Tselem views the detention of 'Eid a serious breach of the freedom
of activity of a human rights organization, and calls on the
Palestinian Authority to release him immediately. B'Tselem considers
the Palestinian Authority responsible for the health and safety
of Bassem 'Eid.
<P>
<HR>
