<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE> B'Tselem - Beatings, Maltreatment and Degradation </TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY  BGCOLOR="FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000">

<CENTER>
<I>
<FONT SIZE="+2"><B><NOBR>
	Beatings, Maltreatment and Degradation
	of Palestinians <WBR> By Israeli Police Officers 
	During June - July 1996
</NOBR></B></FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE="+1"><B> September 1996 </B></FONT>
</I>
<HR>
<P>
- Summary -
</CENTER>
<P>

<FONT SIZE=+2><B>T</B></FONT>he report presents eleven cases based on testimony
of the victims and eye-witnesses.  Ten cases concern violence by police 
officers and Border Police officers.  One incident concerns a municipal 
inspector.  In all cases, illegitimate and often brutal force was used 
against Palestinians, including children.  Some of the Palestinian victims 
were hospitalized as a result of injuries suffered in these incidents.
<P>
B'Tselem forwarded all the testimonies, together with relevant medical 
documents, to the Department for the Investigation of Police Officers, of 
the Ministry of Justice, and to other official bodies, and requested that 
the cases be investigated. To date, B'Tselem has not been informed of the 
results of any investigation. 
<P>
In almost all of the cases, the Palestinian victims entered Israel without 
permits, were beaten and then returned to the Occupied Territories.  This 
pattern suggests an unwritten policy to deter Palestinians from entering 
Israel without a permit by using violence and degradation. In its conclusion, 
B'Tselem demands that those responsible for security and enforcement of the 
law must totally eradicate this phenomenon.
<P>
<B><A HREF="96sept.exe"> Download full report </A></B><BR>
Run the file you have downloaded to extract the text file.


