<HEAD>
<TITLE> B'Tselem - Annual Report 1990-1991 </TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY  BGCOLOR="FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000">

<CENTER>
<I>
<FONT SIZE="+3"><B> Annual Report 1990-1991 </B></FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE="+2"><B> Violations of Human Rights in The Occupied Territories </B></FONT><BR>
</I>
<HR>
<P>
- Summary -
</CENTER>
<P>

<FONT SIZE=+1><B><U>Table of Contents </U></B></Font>
<OL>
<LI><B> Introduction: </B><BR>
     Fatalities<BR>
     Injuries<BR>
     Obstructions to the neutrality of medical services<BR>
     House demolition and sealing<BR>
     Curfew
<P>
<LI><B> Detention, trials, and incarceration: </B><BR>
     Detention<BR>
     Administrative detention<BR>
     Military courts in the territories<BR>
     Detention facilities<BR>
     Deportations<BR>
     Deterioration of the education system<BR>
     Limitations on freedom of expression and freedom of information <BR>
<P>
<LI><B> Discriminatory law enforcement: </B><BR>
     Unequal treatment of Jews and Arabs <BR>
     Family separation and reunification<BR>
     Discrimination in planning and supervision of building <BR>
     Tax collection<BR>
<P>
<LI><B> Appendix: </B><BR>
     Preliminary response of the IDF spokesperson to the report.
</OL>     
The report is based on B'Tselem's investigations during 1990-1991. <BR>
Some findings were published previously and were
been updated for this report, and others appear for the first
time. This report is concerned with human rights
infringements committed directly or indirectly by the Government
of Israel in the territories under its rule.  

<P>
