<HEAD>
<TITLE> B'Tselem - Information Sheet Update </TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY  BGCOLOR="FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000">

<CENTER>
<I>
<FONT SIZE="+3"><B> Information Sheet: </B></FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE="+2"><B> Update </B></FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE="+1"><B> September 1989 </B></FONT>
</I>
<HR>
<P>
- Summary -
</CENTER>
<P>


<B>Intifada Fatalities:</B>
<UL>
     <LI> Total deaths during the Intifada
     <LI> 46% of August fatalities - aged 16 or less
</UL>

<B> Fatalities Due to Unexplained Circumstances: </B>
<UL>
     At least 11 Palestinian residents of the territories were
     wounded during the month of August 1989 under unexplained
     circumstances. B'Tselem approached the Minister of Defence
     and the Minister of Police, presented them with descriptions
     of the following exceptional incidents, and noted the
     increase of such incidents relative to previous months.
     B'Tselem also noted that these incidents largely took place
     in the Judea area and that the victims were particularly young.
</UL>

<B>Administrative Detention:</B>
<UL>
     <LI> Lengthening the term of administrative detention
     <LI> New regulations: more severe means of punishment against
      administrative detainees
</UL>

