<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=+3><B><I>Urgent Action:</I>
<P>
Right to Education of Gaza Students</B></FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=+2.5> Petition of Israeli Academics</FONT></CENTER>
<P>
<HR>
The following petition will be published in the Hebrew press.  
The petition will be signed by Israeli faculty members.  
If you are affiliated with an Israeli university and wish to sign the petition, 
please send us your name and the name of the institution you are affiliated with. 
<p>
We would be grateful for a contribution of NIS 50 per faculty member to cover the cost of publication.
<p>
Contributions can be sent to the BíTselem office:
<p>
<CENTER>43 Emek Refaim St * Jerusalem 93141 </CENTER>
<P>
	We would very much appreciate your passing this petition on to other university faculty.
<p>
For more information, contact Eitan Felner at BíTselem:
<P><center>Telephone: 02-5617271<BR>
Fax: 02-5610756<BR>
e-mail: btselem@actcom.co.il</center>
<p>
<p>
<HR>
<P>

<B><FONT SIZE=+2.5><CENTER>LET THEM STUDY!</center></font></B>
<p>
We, faculty members of Israel's institutions of higher education, urge the Israeli government to enable some 1,200 Gaza students to reach their schools in the West Bank.
<P>
We maintain that "security considerations" cannot justify a sweeping and collective restriction on hundreds of persons, particularly since they only need to cross a short distance through Israeli territory, which can be easily arranged and secured.
<P>
We believe that education is a fundamental right, and that preventing Gaza students from exercising this right not only harms the individual students, but also impedes the advancement and development of Palestinian society as a whole.  Consequently, the chances for peace between the two peoples is also harmed.
<P>
<P>
