<center><A NAME="no.5"><h3>5. RECENT PROJECT -TYPE DOMESTIC RESEARCHES</h3></center>



<p>



    The studies carried out in Forestry and Forest Products Research Institute are very important to indicate some scientifical basic concepts necessary for Forestry Agency's pressing a policy on forest

 forestry and forest products. To satisfy these administrative needs

 many long-term research programs and/or projects are going on not only by the budget of Ministry of Agriculture

 Forestry and Fisheries

 but also by Science and Technology Agency

 Environment Agency and others.

<blockquote>







1) Comprehensive research on elucidation and most suitable control method of stability of



ecosystem [1989 - 1998]



<br>2) Marketing strategies for domestic timber [1991 - 1997]



<br>3) Comprehensive research on utilization of new bio-materials [1990 - 2000]



<br>4) Natural regeneration techniques by aid of mechanical power on the sloping site  [1991-



1995]



<br>5) Evaluation of the global warming effects on plants (Global warming effects on the



distribution pattern of natural vegetation in Japan)  [1993 - 1995]



<br>6) Mechanism of reduction of genetic variation in endangered wildlife [1993 - 1995]



<br>7) Quality improvement and highly-developed manufacturing techniques for Sugi (Performance evaluation of newly designed wood products from Sugi) [1994 - 1996]



<br>8) Research on socioeconomic conditions for encouragement of the less favored areas [1994 -



1996]



<br>9) Ecology boards using recycled paper resources [1994 - 1996]



<br>10) Analysis of the occurrence mechanism of resinous stem canker of the hinoki cypress and



the development of techniques for controlling the disease [1994 - 1997]



<br>11) Establishing technique for  of a long term research site based on digitalized information



maps of the preservation beech forest in Shiragami mountains [1995 - 1996]  



<br>12) Elucidation of the soil degradation mechanisms in artificial coniferous forests [1995 -



1997]



<br>13) Development of forest management vehicle and construction of utilization system  [1995



- 1997]



<br>14) Studies on engineered properties of wood and wood based materials for seismic design



[1995 - 1997]



<br>15) Analysis environment change based on forest monitoring [1995 - 1999]



<br>16) The restoration  and management techniques of Ogasawara forest ecosystem [1995-



1999]



<br>16) Genomic analysis of pathogenic microorganisms and their application for diagnosis and



identification [1995 - 2000]



</blockquote>



