<title>FORESTRY WHITE PAPER</title>
<pre>
       <h2>FORESTRY WHITE PAPER</h2>
       <h4>Fiscal Year 1993</h4>
       <h3>SUMMRY</h3>

<img src="white-p_93/w-p_photo.gif">
          <h2>Forestry Agency , JAPAN</h2>
</pre>
<HR>
<pre>
This is the summry of the "Annual Report on Trends of Forestry
(Fiscal year 1993)"and "Forestry Policy Actions to Be Taken in
Foscal Year 1994"which were laid before the Diet in conformity
with the Forestry Basic Law(1964),Article 9,Clause 1 and 2 
respectively,and were approved on 15th April 1994.


[Cover Page Photo:Kozakawa-cho,Wakayama prefecture]
<P>
<HR>
<pre><br>
<B><h3>CONTENTS</B></h3>
<br> 
<A HREF="white-p_93/t1.html"><B>1.TOWARD THE EPOCH OF FOREST AND TREES</B></A> 
 Retrospect of 30 years of forest/forestry and wood industries,
 and prospects 
(Prologue)
 1 Changes in forest/forestry and wood industries over the past 
   30 years 
 2 Toward the epoch of forest and trees 

<A HREF="white-p_93/t2.html"><B>2.FORESTRY AND VILLAGES IN UPSTREAM AREAS</B></A> 
 1 Recent trends in forestry production 
 2 Recent trends in forestry management 
 3 Damage to forests and countermeasures 
 4 Recent trends in upstream villages 

<A HREF="white-p_93/t3.html"><B>3.ROLE OF NATIONAL FOREST OPERATION AND MANAGEMENT REFORM</B></A>
 1 Role of National Forest Operation and progress of its under-
   takings 
 2 Implementation of management reform and new endeavors 

<A HREF="white-p_93/t4.html"><B>4.WOOD DEMAND/SUPPLY AND WOOD INDUSTRIES</B></A> 
 1 Recent trends in wood demand and supply 
 2 Recent trends in wood prices
 3 Recent trends in wood industries

<A HREF="white-p_93/t5.html"><B>5.WORLD FOREST RESOURCES AND JAPAN'S INTERNATIONAL FOREST/FORE-
  STRY COOPERATION</B></A> 
 1 State of world forest resources, global environmental issues,
   and wood trade 
 2 Japan's effort for international forest/forestry cooperation

<A HREF="white-p_93/t6.html"><B>Epilogue</B></A>

<A HREF="white-p_93/t7.html"><B>FORESTRY POLICY ACTIONS TAKEN IN 1993</B></A> 

<A HREF="white-p_93/t8.html"><B>FORESTRY POLICY ACTIONS TO BE TAKEN IN 1994</B></A>
</pre>
<HR>
<B>ABBREVIATIONS</B> 

<P>
<pre>
CIFOR - Center for International Forestry Research 
FY    - Japanese Fiscal Year (1st April - 31st March of the 
        following year) 
FAO   - Food and Agriculture Organization ofthe United Nations 
GATT  - General Agreement on Tariff and Trade 
GDP   - Gross Domestic Products 
ICRAE - International Center for Research in Agroforestry 
ITTA  - International Tropical Timber Agreement 
ITTO  - International Tropical Timber Organization 
JICA  - Japan International Cooperation Agency 
LVL   - Laminated Veneer Lumber 
MAFF  - Ministry of Agriculture. Forestry and Fisheries 
MoC   - Ministry of Construction 
MoF   - Ministry of Finance 
MoL   - Ministry of Labor 
NGO   - Non Government Organization 
OECD  - Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development 
OISCA - Organization for Industrial, Spiritual and Cultural 
        Advancement 
TFAP  - Tropical Forests Action Program 
UNCED - United Nations Conference on Environment and Development 
</pre>
