<B><h2>3 ROLE OF NATIONAL FOREST OPERATION AND MANAGEMENT REFORM</B></h2> 
<P>
<h3><B>1 Role of National Forest Operation and the progress of Its undertakings </h3></B>
Role of National Forest O eration 
<br>+ It is expected to play an important role as the core of Japan's forest/forestry i.e. 
public benefit functions, a sustainable supply of forest products on a programmed 
basis, and contribution to local economy. 
<br>. 20% of total land area, 30% of forest area, 1/4 of domestic timber supply 
<br>.Forest management by function types: national land conservation forest, nature 
preservation forest, total utilization forest, and timber production forest. 
<br>. Active participation in establishing river basin forest management systems. 
<br>Public benefit functions 
<br>+ The Forest Biosphere ReseNes for Yakushima and Shirakarni Mountain Range 
will be registered on the Natural Heritage List underthe Convention for the 
Protection of the World Cultural and Natural Heritage. 
<br>Closeness to nature 
<br>+ The National Forest Operation is promoting Profit Sharing Silviculture (Green 
Owner) that co-finances with the state and fosters forest, in response to the 
growing movement to participate in nurturing forest. 
<br>. "Corporate Forest' is being supported by 8 companies for Middle-term Profit-
sharing Silviculture and 6 companies for Long-term Profit-sharing Afforestation. 
<br>. Human Green Plan is being implemented at 23 sites. 
<br>Timber supply 
<br>+ The National Forest Operation is actively promoting sales and extension of logs 
and sawn timber of "Dry Logs" (natura[ly dried stems without limbing). 
<br>. In 1992 the NFO supplied 7.18 million m3. 
<P>
<h3><B>2 Implementation of management reform and new endeavors</h3></B> 
Financial situation 
<br>+ The NFO is still under severe financial situation due to the difficulty of securing 
revenue as a result of reduced harvesting volume, and to the increasing payment 
of interest and capital on the accumulated debt. 
 <br>Mana ement reform 
 <br>+ Based on the new Reform Plan formulated in July 1 991 , the NFO is making efforts 
to achieve revenue/expenses balance for the ordinary operating areas by the 
year 2000 such as organizational simplification and rationalization, and 
downsizing the employment to appropriate level. 
 <br>New endeavors 
 <br>+ Long-term agreements were made with 30 forestry enterprises by the end of 
December 1993, which ensures stable and long-term combined contractual 
agreements for log production, silviculture, thinning and sales. 
 <br>+ With the creation of Rare Wildlife Protection & Control Project, control of habitat 
is being implemented for such species as blakistone fish owls, Japanese cranes, 
etc.s 
<P>
<img src="fig-21.gif">
<P>
