<B><h2>FORESTRY POLICY ACTIONS TAKEN IN 1993</B></h2> 
<P>
Improvement of diverse forests as sources of green and water both for private and 
national forests. 
<P>Improvement of conditions for forestry production, processing and distribution to 
realize "the epoch of domestic timber". 
<P>Augmentation of forestry production 
<P>+ Vitalization of forestry production with the river basin as a unit and promotion of 
appropriate forest management: 
<br>1) Establishment of effective forest Plans both for private and national forests; 
<br>2) Formation of road networks to enable effective forest work, improvement of living 
environment, promotion of uneven-aged forest and tended natural forest, 
activation of forestry in each river basin by securing seedlings of good quality, 
promotion of thinning; 
<br>3) Improvement of forestry technology, enhancement of labor safety, research and 
development, development of high performance forestry machinery. 
<P>Forestry structure improvement 
<P>+ Vitalization of forestry and villages in upstream areas: 
<br>In the areas where forestry occupies an important Position, promotion of high-
density road networks, highly efficient Production, improvement of processing 
and distribution facilities, forestry experience, facilities for village-city exchange, 
improvement of living environment in upstream areas. 
<P>Im rovement of wood distribution system strengthening of wood industries and 
stabilization of wood demand and supply 
<P>+ Improvement of wood distribution system and strengthening of wood industries: 
<br>1) Streamlining of a low-cost stable supply system of timber from production to 
processing and distribution, establishing a brand name for local timber and 
market Promotion; 
<br>2) Extension and education of wood use, collection and analysis of information 
necessary for improvement of wood distribution and modernization of 
management;  
<br>+ Expansion of wood demand, and stabilization of wood demand/supply and prices: 
<br>1) Development of wood utilization technology as housing components, 
construction of large wooden buildings, promotion of wooden interior materials 
for public facilities, and development of new wood utilization technologies; 
<br>2) Introduction of high performance equipment, restructuring and realignment of 
wood industrial estates, formulation of wood industries' vision, restructuring and 
realignment of forestry enterprises; 
<br>3) Collection, analysis and dissemination of information by the Central Council for 
Wood Demand and Supply. 
<P>Improvement of forestry worker`s welfare and human resource development 
<P>+ Improvement of welfare of forest workers, and nurturing successors of forestry: 
<br>1) Coordination with school education, facilitation of entry into forestry for new 
workforce, support for group activities; 
<br>2) Stabilization of employment, reduction of labor intensity, establishment of River 
Basin Forestry Sevice Centers. 
<P>Improvement of forestry loan and taxation 
<P>+ Vitalization of forestry production and strengthening of management basis: 
<br>1) Creation of new funds, revision of loan conditions, and enlargement of loans; 
<br>2) Special reduction for forest Planning from forest income, exceptional measures 
of counting planting expenses as loss, and creation of an increased depreciation 
system for forestry machinery owned by logging enterprises. 
<P>Public benefit functions of forest 
<P>+ Land and water conservation: 
<br>Designation and proper management of protection forest, forest improvement in 
watershed areas, and prevention of disasters in mountainous areas; 
<br>+ Heightened awareness of the national greening concept, and improvement of 
forest resources with participation of the general public: 
<br>Promotion of greening activities centering on "Green Day", and consolidation of 
the Forest Fund for Green and Water'. 
<P>Vitalization of village in upstream areas 
<P>+ Contribution to local economies: 
<br>Increased production of non-timber forest Products and formation of specialized 
producing districts, infrastructure improvement for dwelling in forest, 
implementation of the special measure "Holidays in upstream villages" which 
attempts to realize long-term resident leisure linked closely with the "Contact 
with green hometown project" of local governments. 
<P>Administration and management of National Forest 
<P>+ Improvement of the financial Position of National Forest Operation: 
Based on the Management Reform Plan and in cooperation with the private 
forests, efficiency improvement for various undertakings in conformity with the 
river basin forest management system, and appropriate forest management 
according to the forest functions classification.
<P>Other measures
<P>+Strengthening of forstry associations:
<br>Promotion of wide area merger of forest owners` associations in order for
consolidation of an organizational and managerial base.
<br>+Contribution to conservation of forest resources in developing countries:
<br>Local forestry development cooperation,and hosting international conferences for
 forest conservation and establishment,and sustainable forest  management.
<P>In order to implement the above mwasures,\736.2 billion(\544.3 billion in the previous year)
was budgeted for the general account,and 678.3 billion (\628.5 billion)
for the National Forest Operation Special Account.
<P>Mearsures related to "Study Group of Forest and Upstream Villages"
<br>Since cooperation among government offices is indispensable for solving problems
of forest and upstream villages,the "Study Group of Forest and Upstream Villages"
established by the national Land Agency and the Ministry of Home Affairs discussed
concrete measures including utilization of the local allocation tax.
<P>
<img src="fig-33.gif">
<P>
