<B><h2>FORESTRY POLICY ACTIONS TO BE TAKEN IN 1994 </B></h2>
<P>
Improvement of diverse forest as sources of "green and water' both for private and 
national forests. 
<P>Improvement of conditions for forestry production, processing and distribution to 
realize the "epoch of domestic timber". 
<P>Promotion of international forest/forestry cooperation for conservation of the global 
environment. 
<P>Augmentation of forestry production 
<br>+ Vitalization of forestry production with the river basin as a unit, upgrading of forest 
improvement, and improvement of forestry productivity: 
<br>1) Establishment of effective forest Plans both for the private and national forests; 
<br>2) Formation of road networks to enable effective forest work, improvement of living 
environment, promotion of uneven-aged forest work and tended natural forest 
work, vitalization of river basin forestry by securing seedlihgs of good quality, 
and promotion of thinning; 
<br>3) Promotion of research and development and development of high performance 
forestry machinery to improve forestry technology and forestry productivity. 
<P>Forestry structure improvement 
<br>+ Vitalization of forestry and villages in upstream areas: 
<br>In the areas where forestry occupies an important position, high-density road 
networks, highly efficient production, improvement of processing and distribution 
facilities, forestry experience, facilities for city-village exchange, improvement of 
living environment. 
<P>Improvement of the domestic timber distribution system strengthenin of wood 
industries,and stabilization of demand and supply of wood 
<br>+ Improvement of the domestic timber distribution system and strengthening of wood 
industries: 
<br>1) Streamlining of low-cost stable supply system of domestic timber from 
production, processing to distribution, and establishing a brand name for local 
timber and its marketing; 
<br>2) Collection, analysis of information necessary for improvement of timber 
distribution and modernization of management; 
<br>3) Introduction of high performance equipment, restructuring and realignment of 
wood industries, upgrading of wood industries, and strengthening of logging 
enterprises. 
<br>+ Expansion of wood demand, and stabilization of wood demand/supply and prices: 
<br>1) Improvement of supply system of quality sawn timber, development of wood 
utilization technology as housing components, distribution of highly processed 
wood products, promotion of new wood utilization technologies; 
<br>2) Collection, analysis, and dissemination of information on demand/supply and 
price by the Central Council for Wood Demand and Supply. 
<P>Improvement of fore t workers' welfare and human resources development 
<br>+ Improving forest workers' welfare and nurturing successors of forestry: 
<br>1) Coordination with school education, inducement of new workforce into forestry 
and its institutionalization, and support to group activities; 
<br>2) Stabilization of employment, improvement of employment conditions and 
reduction of labor intensity by total application of the Labor Standard Law, and 
introduction of labor environment improvement facilities; 
<br>3) Consolidation of labor safety and sanitation, and safety control measures 
corresponding to mechanization. 
<P>Improvement of forest loans and taxation 
<br>+ Vitalization of forestry production and strengthening of management basis: 
<br>1)Creation of a new fund (interest-free silvicultural loan), revision of loan 
conditions, and enlargement of loans 
<br>2) Exceptional treatment of corporate tax on the mutual fund program run by the 
National Federation of Forest Owners' Association, special treatment of income 
tax and corporate tax on the acquisition of lay-up equipment (Plywood 
manufacturing machinery), creation of a petroleum purchase tax concerning 
bark manure manufactures. 
<P>Public benefit functions of forest 
<br>+ Land and water conservation: 
<br>Designation and proper management of protection forest, forest improvement in 
watershed areas, rehabilitation of dilapidated forest to secure stable supply of 
quality water and establishment of water quality conservation facilities, and land 
conservation projects for prevention of mountain disasters. 
<br>+ Heightened awareness of the national greening concept, and forest resources 
<br>improvement with participation of the general public: 
Promotion of greening activities centering on "Green Day", and enlargement of 
the "Forest Fund for Green and Water". 
<P>Vitalization of villages in upstream areas 
<br>+ Contribution to local economies: 
<br>Increased production of non-timber forest products and formation of specialized 
producing districts, conservation and formation of the scenic beauty of traditional 
forest and mountain villages, promotion of the special project "holidays in 
upstream villages" that attempts to attract long-term resident leisure. 
<P>Administration and management of National Forest 
<br>+ Improvement of the financial position of National Forest Operation: 
<br>based on the management Reform Plan, efficiency needs to be improved for its 
undertakings under the river basin forest management system in cooperation 
with private forests and ensure appropriate forest management according to the 
forest functions classification. 
<P>Promotion of international forest/forestry cooperation 
<br>+ Contribution to the conservation and establishment of forest in developing 
countries: 
<br>1) Local forestry development through bilateral cooperation (technical, financial). 
dispatch of experts and financial contribution to international organization; 
<br>2) Hosting international conferences on tropical forest conservation and 
establishment, nurturing of human resources for promotion of global greening, 
arranging for technical training of forest engineers from developing countries; 
<br>3) Survey, research and technology development for appropriate management of 
tropical forest. 
<P>Other measures 
<br>+ Strengthening of forestry associations: 
<br>Promotion of wide area merger of forest owners' association to solidify 
organization and management basis, assistance to wood demand expansion 
campaigns and events organized by wood processing/distributing 
associations. 
<P>In order to implement the above measures, \479.4 billion (\464.0 billion in previous 
year) will be budgeted for the General Account, and \592.7 billion (\609.8 billion) for 
the National Forest Operation Special Account. 
<P>Measures related to "Study Group of Forest and Upstream Villages" 
<br>Since cooperation among government offices is indispensable for solving problems 
of forest and villages in upstream areas, the "Study Group of Forest and Upstream 
Villages" that was established by the National Land Agency and the Ministry of 
Home Affairs will deliberate various measures including utilization of the local 
allocation tax. 
<P>
