<b>FORESTRY POLICY ACTIONS TAKEN IN FY 1994</b> 
<p>
Improvement of diverse forests as the sources of "green 
and water' for both private and national forests. 
<br>
Improvement of conditions for forestry production, 
processing and distribution to realize the "epoch of 
domestic timber" 
<p>
Promotion of forest production
<ul>
<li>Vitalization of forestry production with the river 
basin as a unit, upgrading of forest improvement:
<br>
1) Establishment of effective forest plans for both 
private and national forests; 
<br>
2) Formation of road networks to enable efficient 
forest management, improvement of living circumstances, 
promotion of multi-storied forest management and tended 
natural forest management, vitalization of river basin 
forestry by securing genetically superior seedlings, 
and promotion of thinning; 
<br>
3) Promotion of research and development and development 
of high performance forestry machinery to improve forestry 
technology and labor safety. 
</ul>
Structural improvement in forestry
<ul>
<li>Vitalization of forestry and villages in upstream areas: 
<br>In the area where forestry occupies an important 
position, establishment of high-density road networks, 
promotion of highly efficient production, improvement 
of processing and distribution facilities, provision 
of opportunities for forestry experience, establishment 
of facilities for city-village exchanges, and improvement 
of living circumstances. 
</ul>
Improvement of the forest roducts distribution system 
strengthening of wood industries and stabilization of 
demand and supply of wood
<ul>
<li>Improvement of the forest products distribution 
system and strengthening of wood industries: 
<br>
l) Streamlining the supply system of domestic timber 
which integrates production, processing, and distribution 
stages, and establishing brand names for local timber 
to promote their marketing; 
<br>
2) Extension and enhancement of wood utilization, 
collection, and analysis of information necessary for 
improving timber distribution and modernizing the
 management of wood industries. 
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Expansion of wood demand, and stabilization of wood 
demand, supply and prices:
<br>
1) Improvement of supply system of high quality lumber, 
development of wood utilization technology as housing 
components, development of new wood utilization technologies; 
<br>
2) Upgrading of wood industries, and strengthening of logging 
enterprises; 
<br>
3) Collection, analysis, and dissemination of information 
on wood demand, supply and so forth. 
</ul>
Improvement of forest workers' welfare and human resources 
development
<ul>
<li>Improving forestry workers' welfare and nurturing successors 
of forestry: 
<br>
1) Coordination with school education, inducement of new work 
force into forestry, and support to group activities; 
<br>
2) Improvement of employment conditions such as stabilization 
of employment and reduction of labor intensity. 
</ul>
Improvement of forest loans and taxation
<ul>
<li>Vitalization of forestiy production and strengthening 
of management basis: 
<br>
1) Creation of a new fund (comprehensive support for advanced 
forestry areas), revision of loan conditions, and enlargement 
of loans; 
<br>
2) Exceptional treatment of corporate tax on the mutual fund 
program run by the National Federation of Forest Owners' 
Association, special treatment of income tax and corporate tax 
on the acquisition of lay-up equipment. 
</ul>
Public benefit functions of forests
<ul>
<li> Land and water conservation: 
<br>
Designation and proper management of protection forests, 
forest improvement in watershed areas, and land conservation 
projects for prevention of mountain disasters.
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Dissemination of the national greening concept, and 
forest resources improvement with participation of the 
general public: 
<br>
Promotion of greening activities centering on the "Green Day", 
and enlargement of the "Forest Fund for Green and Water" 
</ul>
Vitalization of upstream villages
<ul>
<li>Contribution to local economies: 
<br>
1) Increased production of non-timber forest products and 
formation of specialized production districts; 
<br>
2) Conservation and creation of scenic beauty of traditional 
forest and mountain villages, project to promote long-stay 
leisure activities, improvement of key facilities for city-village 
exchanges. 
</ul>
Administration and management of National Forest
<ul>
<li>Improvement of the financial situation of National 
Forest Operation: 
<br>Based on the Management Reform Plan, efficiency of operation 
needs to be improved under the river basin forest management 
system in cooperation with private forests and by ensuring 
appropriate forest management according to the forest 
functions classifioation. 
</ul>
Promotion of international forest and forestry cooperation
<ul>
<li> Contribution to sustainable management of global 
forests including tropical forest: 
<br>
Hosting international conferences on conservation and 
establishment of tropical forest, and on sustainable 
forest management, developing human resources, carrying 
out surveys, research, and developing technology for 
appropriate management of tropical forests. 
</ul>
Other Measures
<ul>
<li>Strengthening of forestry asscciations:
<br>
Promotion of wide area merger of forest owners' associations 
to solidify organization and management basis.
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Aid to the Great Hanshin-Awaji Earthquake: 
<br>
Measures for stable supply of wood, early restoration of 
the devastated mountain slopes, financial assistance to 
the damaged forestry and wood product industries. 
</ul>
In order to implement the above measures, <img src="yen.GIF">535.8 billion (<img src="yen.GIF">736.2 
billion in the previous year) was budgeted in the General 
Account, and <img src="yen.GIF">597.3 billion(<img src="yen.GIF">678.3 billion) in the National 
Forest Operation Special Account. 
<p>
<pre>
      Forestry related general account budget (millon yen) 
<hr>
Items                                       FY 1993     FY 1994
<hr>
