</pre>
<p>
Measures related to "Study Group on Forests and Upstream Villages"
<ul>
<li>Since cooperation among government offices is indispensable 
for solving problems of forests and villages in upstream 
areas,the "Study Group on Forests and Upstream Villages"
 was established by the Forestry Agency, the National Land 
Agency and the Ministry of Home Affairs. Based on the 
discussions of the Group: 
<br>
1) Creation of a "Nurturing Rich Forest" project, promotion 
of intensified measures to nurture successors in forestry. 
<br>
2) Financial support for the purchase of upstream forests 
by local governments. 
</DOC>
