<b>FORESTRY POLICY ACTIONS TO BE TAKEN IN FY 1995</b>
<p>
improvement of diverse forests as the sources of national 
forests. 
<br>
Improvement of conditions for forestly production, the 
"epoch of domestic timber". 
<p> 
Promotion of forest roduction
<ul>
<li>Vitalization of forestry production with the river 
basin as a unit, upgrading of forest improvement, and 
improvement of forestry productivity: 
<br>
1) Establishment of effective forest plans for both 
private and naticnal forests; 
<br>
2) Formation of road networks to enable efficient 
forest management, improvement of living circumstances, 
promotion of multi-storied forest management and tended 
natural forest management, vitalization of river basin 
forestly by securing genetically superior seedlings, 
and promotion of thinning; 
<br>
3) Promotion of research and development, and development 
of high performance forestry machinery jn order to improve 
forestry technology and forestry productivity. 
</ul>
Structural improvement in forestry
<ul>
<li>Vitalization of forestry and villages in upstream areas: 
<br>
1) In the area where forestry occupies an important position, 
establishment of high-density road networks, improvement of 
production, processing and distribution facilities: 
<br>
2) Provision of opportunities for forestry experience, 
establishment of facilities for city-village exchanges, 
and improvement of living environment facilities; 
<br>
3)In the hilly mountainous areas, raising successors of 
forest management, with establishing necessary facilities, 
and solidifying wood supply system in the model river basins. 
</ul>
Improvement of the forest products supply sytem,promotion of 
wood utilization and stabilization of demand and supply of wood 
<ul>
<li>For improvement of forest products supply system and 
promotion of wood utilization: 
<br>
1) Enhancement of log production efficiency, standardization 
and higher-degree processing of housing materials, development 
and practioal use of building techniques by using pre-cut 
lumber and new woody materials, and establishment of efficient 
and stable wood supply system that integrates production, 
processing, and distribution; 
<br>
2) Formulation of basic policy for the promotion of wood 
utilization, promotion of local wood utilization, development 
of wood utilization technology, and creation of new use of 
wood by technology development; 
<br>
3) Introduction of high-performance equipment, reorganizing 
and upgrading of wood industries, and strengthening of log 
production enterprises. 
</ul>
<ul>
<li>In order to stabilize wood demand, supply and prices: 
<br>
Collection, analyses, and dissemination of comprehensive 
information about wood, differentiation of looal non-timber 
forest products, disaster prevention measures, and establishment 
of supply system that meets demand and supply trends. 
</ul>
Improvement of forest workers' welfare and human resources 
development
<ul>
<li>In order to Improve forestry workers' welfare and 
nurture successors of forestry: 
<br>
1) Coordination with school education and local communities, 
inducement of new work force into forestry, voluntary 
studies by forestry successors, and support to group 
activities; 
<br>
2) Improvement of employment conditions such as stabilization 
of employment and reduction of labor intensity, promotion 
of memberships to Forestry Workers Retirement Plan and social 
security systems; 
<br>
3) Improvement of labor safety and sanitation,preventjon 
of labor accidents, preventive measures against vibration 
disease, and guidance of safety methods. 
</ul>
Improvement of forest loans and taxation
<ul>
<li>In order to vitalize forestry production and to 
strengthen management basis: 
<br>
1) Relaxation of loan conditions and enlargement of loan 
amount; 
<br>
2) Shortening the taxational amortization of shiitake 
bed logs from the current 4 years to 2, special deduction 
to forest income, exceptional deduction of planting costs, 
plantation reserve, and continuation of increased 
depreciation of forestry machinery owned by log 
production enterprises. 
</ul>
Public benefit functions of forests
<ul>
<li>For land and water conservation: 
<br>
Designation and proper administration of protection 
forests, forest improvement in watershed areas, 
improvement of coastline forests, forest nurturing for 
conservation and creation of green-rich living circumstances,
improvement of land conservation and disaster preventive projects.
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Dissemination of the national greening concept, 
forest resources improvement with participation of the 
general public: 
<br>
Promotion of greening activities centering on the 
"Green Day", and enlargement of the "Forest Fund for 
Green and Water"
</ul>
Vitalization of upstream villages
<ul>
<li>In order to contribute to local economies: 
<br>
1) Estabiishment of local brands for non-timber forest products; 
<br>
2) Conservation and creation of scenic beauty of traditional 
forest and mountain villages, and improvement of the special 
project to attract long-term residing holiday goers; 
<br>
3) Improvement of the infrastructure for forestry production 
and living environment. 
</ul>
Administration and management of National Forest
<ul>
<li>In view of the current financial situation: 
<br>
Based on the Management Reform Plan, efficiency of operation 
needs to be improved under the river basin forest management 
system in cooperation with private forests and by 
implementing appropriate forest management according 
to the forest functions classification. 
</ul>
Promotion of international forest and forest cooperation
<ul>
<li>In order to contribute to sustainable management of 
global forests especially including tropical forest: 
<br>
1) Promotion of bilateral forestry cooperation (technical 
and financial), and support to international organizations 
through dispatch of experts and financial contribution; 
<br>
2) Hosting Senior Foresters' Conference on Tropical Forest 
Conservation, active participation in international 
endeavors, human resouroe development for implementation 
of international greening cooperation, and technical 
training for foresters from developing countries; 
<br>
3) Research, surveys, and technology development for 
appropriate management of tropical forests. 
</ul>
Other Measures
<ul>
<li>In order to assist and strengthen forestry organizations: 
<br>
Promotion of wide area merger of forest owners' associations 
to solidify organization and management basis, financial 
assistance to wood use promotion activities organized by 
wood processing and distribution associations. 
</ul>
In order to carry out above measures, <img src="yen.GIF">501.7 biilion (<img src="yen.GIF">479.3 
billion in the previous year) will be budgeted in the General 
Account, and <img src="yen.GIF">587.3 billion (<img src="yen.GIF">592.7 billion) in the National 
Forest Operation Special Account. 
<p>
Measures related to "Study Group on Forests and Upstream 
Villages" 
<ul>
<li>Since cooperation among govemment offices is 
indispensable for solving the issues of forests and 
upstream villages, the Study Group which was established 
by the Forestry Agency, the National Land Agency, and the 
Ministry of Home Affairs will deliberate further on various 
issues including looal finance and taxation and put forward 
concrete measures. 
</ul>
</DOC>
